[[ファイル:Heda torii.jpg|thumb|250px|Torii]]
[[ファイル:Fuji (37929951324).jpg|thumb|250px|{{ill|lt=Mihama Cape|Q11489198|qid=Q11489198|1=Cape Mihama}}, torii, and {{ill|lt=Mount Fuji|Q39231|qid=Q39231|1=Mount Fuji}}]]
'''Morokuchi Shrine''' (もろくちじんじゃ<ref>[https://numazukanko.jp/fc/location/50018 Morokuchi Shrine] - Numazu City Tourism Strategy Division</ref>, also read もろぐちじんじゃ<ref>[http://www.shizuoka-jinjacho.or.jp/shokai/jinja.php?id=4402126 Morokuchi Shrine] - Shizuoka Prefectural Shrine Association</ref>) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Heda Village (Shizuoka)|Q5697064|qid=Q5697064|lt=Heda|1=Heda, Shizuoka}}, {{ill|lt=Numazu|Q241037|qid=Q241037|1=Numazu}}, {{ill|lt=Shizuoka Prefecture|Q131320|qid=Q131320|1=Shizuoka Prefecture}}.

It is located facing east at the tip of {{ill|lt=Mihama Cape|Q11489198|qid=Q11489198|1=Cape Mihama}}. A red torii visible even from the opposite shore stands along the sea in front.

It is jointly managed by the priest of {{ill|lt=Heda Shrine|Q92443788|qid=Q92443788|1=Heda Shrine}} in the same Heda district<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20210920093819/https://ananweb.jp/news/373262/amp/ Hiroyuki Ehara: "I felt immeasurable energy" - two spiritual spots in Numazu] - {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=anan|1=UNKNOWN}} 2021/9/18</ref>.

=== Overview ===
Founding is unknown. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}} presumed to be one of the two "Kunitama-no-Mikoto Shrines" listed in the {{ill|lt=Naka District, Izu Province section|Q11380552|qid=Q11380552|lt=Naka District section of Izu Province|1=List of Shikinaisha in Izu Province}} in the '{{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}'.

From the Jinmyōchō description, the original enshrined deities are inferred as "Moroki-hime, Kunitama-hime, and Tachibana-hime," and the present name "Morokuchi" is thought to derive from that "Moroki"<ref name="yuisho">Precinct origin board</ref>. As a goddess, it was long identified with {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Benten|1=UNKNOWN}} and revered by fishermen<ref name="yuisho"/>.

In August {{ill|lt=1879|Q7783|qid=Q7783|1=1879}} ({{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|qid=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}} 12), it was designated village shrine. The current shrine building was rebuilt in April {{ill|lt=1953|Q18585|qid=Q18585|1=1953}} ({{ill|lt=Shōwa|Q327567|qid=Q327567|1=Shōwa era}} 28)<ref name="yuisho"/>.

=== Enshrined deity ===
* {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Ototachibana-hime-no-Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}}

=== Precinct ===
* Shrine building
* Precinct shrine
* {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Temizuya|1=UNKNOWN}}
* {{ill|lt=Torii|Q234731|qid=Q234731|1=Torii}} (front east side and rear southwest side)

=== Cultural properties ===
* Morokuchi Shrine's {{ill|lt=waniguchi|Q11674315|qid=Q11674315|1=Waniguchi}} (Numazu City designated cultural property<ref>[https://www.city.numazu.shizuoka.jp/shisei/profile/bunkazai/img/ichiran.pdf List of Numazu City designated cultural properties] - Numazu City</ref>)

=== Festivals ===
* Grand annual festival: April 4

=== Surroundings ===
* To the south-southeast in front are beaches such as "Kobunegahama" and "Mihama Beach."
* On the west side behind the shrine are the {{ill|lt=Numazu City Heda Shipbuilding Museum|Q11554523|qid=Q11554523|lt=Heda Shipbuilding Local History Museum|1=Heda Shipbuilding Museum}} and the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Suruga Bay Deep Sea Aquarium|1=UNKNOWN}}.

=== Access ===
* {{ill|lt=Izu-Hakone Railway|Q864568|qid=Q864568|1=Izuhakone Railway}} "{{ill|lt=Shuzenji Station|Q7505799|qid=Q7505799|1=Shuzenji Station}}" then {{ill|lt=Tokai Bus|Q11527778|qid=Q11527778|1=Tokai Bus}} (bound for Heda)
** Get off at "Heda" bus stop, then walk 20 minutes, circling in from the southeast along the coast.

